{"lemma":"سَكَنَ","slug":"سَكَنَ","root":"س.ك.ن","root_slug":"س-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَكَنَ","root":"سكن","pos":"V","occurrence_count":15},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":16},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20250"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be still, to be tranquil, to be peaceful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to calm down, to repose, to rest"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be vowelless, to have no vowel"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abate, to subside, to cease"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pass, to go away, to leave"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trust, to have faith, to be reassured"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feel at home"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to live, to reside, to inhabit (construed with فِي (fī) or بِ (bi) or direct object)","examples":[{"text":"أَسْكُنُ فِي ٱلْقَاهِرَةِ","english":"I live in Cairo"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to calm, to reassure, to appease, to placate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to soothe, to allay, to alleviate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make vowelless, to pronounce without a vowel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَكَنَ (sakana) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"time for rest, means for rest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dwelling, abode, habitation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inhabited area, habitations"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ashes"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew שכן, Akkadian 𒊭𒅗𒉡𒌝 (šakānum, “to place, to put, to set, to establish”) and Ugaritic 𐎌𐎋𐎐 (škn, “to establish”)."},"ipa":["/sa.ka.na/","/sak.ka.na/","/sa.kan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20250","headword_ar":"سَكَنَ","root":"skn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, L, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwnN","text_ar":"سُكُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, L, Msb, K,) said of a thing, (S, L,) of a thing that moves, (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, still, motionless, stationary, in a state of rest, quiet, calm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unruffled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadaA^a","text_ar":"هَدَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Abu-l-'Abbás, L, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qar~a","text_ar":"قَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after motion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its motion"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb;) and in like manner said of a man, and of a beast: (Abu-l-'Abbás, L:) and said of anything such as wind and heat and cold and the like; of rain; [and of pain;] and of anger; [&c.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, still, calm, tranquillized, appeased, allayed, assuaged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quelled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it died away, passed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it remitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subsided; became alleviated, light, slight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and said of a man [or beast or the like, and of a voice or sound],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana Ald~amoEu","text_ar":"سَكَنَ الدَّمْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaA^a","text_ar":"رَقَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the blood, stopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to flow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqAN","text_ar":"رقاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [And one says of heat, and cold, and pain, &c.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana Eanohu","text_ar":"سَكَنَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It passed away from him; quitted him."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanati Aln~aAru","text_ar":"سَكَنَتِ النَّارُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire became extinguished;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became allayed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assuaged; subsided;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to flame"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blaze"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burn fiercely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  [Hence also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a letter)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, quiescent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without a vowel immediately following it; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHar~aka","text_ar":"تَحَرَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana A_ilayohi","text_ar":"سَكَنَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, [where the aor. is said to be"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is either a mistake or rare, for the aor. accord. to common usage is"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the Kur vii.] 189 and xxx. 20,]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwnN","text_ar":"سُكُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He trusted to it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relied upon it, so as to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet, in mind; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakana A_ilayohi","text_ar":"رَكَنَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S and K &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rkn","text_ar":"ركن"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1393},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiTomaA^an~a A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اِطْمَاَنَّ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tmn","text_ar":"طمن"},{"kind":"text","text":";) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotamada Ealayohi","text_ar":"اِعْتَمَدَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waviqa bihi","text_ar":"وَثِقَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he inclined to it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAla A_ilayohi","text_ar":"مَالَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became familiar with it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisutaA^onasa bihi","text_ar":"اِسُتَاْنَسَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifa","text_ar":"اَلِفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; agreeably with explanations here following;] namely, a thing: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana A_ilayohaA","text_ar":"سَكَنَ اـِلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he trusted to her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relied upon her, so as to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet, in mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., as above; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiTomaA^an~a A_ilayohaA","text_ar":"اِطْمَاَنَّ اـِلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ksh and Bd in vii. 189, and Ksh in xxx. 20;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAla A_ilayohaA","text_ar":"مَالَ اـِلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ksh in vii. 189, and the same and Bd in xxx. 20;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaA^onasa bihaA","text_ar":"اِسْتَاْنَسَ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifa","text_ar":"اَلِفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Bd in the same two places;) namely, his wife. (Ksh and Bd.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana Al~adAra","text_ar":"سَكَنَ الَّدارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, Mgh, L, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Ald~aAri","text_ar":"فِى الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmakaAni","text_ar":"بِالمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb, JM,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, Mgh, L, JM) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwnN","text_ar":"سُكُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonN","text_ar":"سُكْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a simple subst., and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"skn","text_ar":"سكن"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, [accord. to which the latter is app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for it is there said that the verb in this case is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaba","text_ar":"طَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the unaugmented inf. n. of which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalabN","text_ar":"طَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanu","text_ar":"سَكَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"I have not found elsewhere, and what is generally used as the inf. n. or quasi-inf. n. of the verb in this case is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isokaAnN","text_ar":"اـِسْكَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as expl. below, (Mgh,) [or rather it is also a subst. in this sense,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inhabited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode in, the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (MA, Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walahu maA sakana fiY A@ll~ayoli waA@ln~ahaAri","text_ar":"وَلَهُ مَا سَكَنَ فِى ا@للَّيْلِ وَا@لنَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [vi. 13], is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ukonaY","text_ar":"السُّكْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ukuwnu","text_ar":"السُّكُونُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd:) if from the former, (Ksh, Bd,) it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To Him belongeth what taketh up its abode in the night and the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Ksh, * Bd, * L, Jel;) meaning, what the night and the day include within their limits: (Ksh, * Bd:) or, if from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ukuwnu","text_ar":"السُّكُونُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, Bd, L,) and what moves; one of the two contraries being mentioned as sufficient [to show what is intended] without the other; (Bd;) app. meaning the creation, collectively, or all created beings. (Abu-l-'Abbás, L.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana","text_ar":"سَكَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misokiyn","text_ar":"مِسْكِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (L, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakuna","text_ar":"سَكُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Askn","text_ar":"اسكن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsk~n","text_ar":"تسكّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamasokana","text_ar":"تَمَسْكَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, K:) and [thus it means particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low, abject, abased, and weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Askn","text_ar":"اسكن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsk~n","text_ar":"تسكّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamasokana","text_ar":"تَمَسْكَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * L;) the former of these being the regular form, (S, L,) and the more common and more chaste; (L;) the latter of them anomalous, [from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almisokiynu","text_ar":"المِسْكِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamanodala","text_ar":"تَمَنْدَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alminodiylu","text_ar":"المِنْدِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamadoraEa","text_ar":"تَمَدْرَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmidoraEapu","text_ar":"المِدْرَعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astkn","text_ar":"استكن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotakaAna","text_ar":"اِسْتَكَانَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb, K) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almasokanapu","text_ar":"المَسْكَنَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ukuwnu","text_ar":"السُّكُونُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"added, (L, Msb,) the vowel of the medial radical letter being thus rendered full in sound, (L, Msb, K,) or it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotafoEala","text_ar":"اِسْتَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkiynapu","text_ar":"الكِينَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “ evil state or condition, ” (Msb,) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkayonu","text_ar":"الكَيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ the [piece of] flesh in the interior of the vulva, ” because he who is lowly and abject is the most obscure of mankind. (L. [See also arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kwn","text_ar":"كون"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kyn","text_ar":"كين"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","L","Msb","K","MA","JM","Ksh","Bd"]}]}}